cs.CR, cs.CY, cs.SI, cs.IR, cs.MM 

This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) as it deals with data protection and tracking sensitive domains. It could also belong to cs.CY (Computers and Society) as it discusses the interplay between privacy and business models of the web. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as it analyzes third-party tracking services. It may also fall under cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as it develops a methodology for annotating websites and extracting tracking services. Finally, it could be classified under cs.MM (Multimedia) as it deals with the inclusion of tracking services on websites.
